	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In my Star Soldier competition hack, I run all of my custom code from WRAM to avoid bankswitching issues (the original game only had 32 KB of PRG ROM). At reset, I swap in the 8 KB bank containing my code, copy the whole thing to $6000-$7FFF, and then swap in the original bank, never touching it again. It feels like cheating, but it works... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

